I just don't think his death is really that believable
I should probably stop ranting about Kilgrave before that's all my blog is
summary: So I just watched the last bit of the AKA Smile again because something’s been bugging me and I figured might as while watch...
body:
So I just watched the last bit of the AKA Smile again because something’s been bugging me and I figured might as while watch just that part to see and I was right.

How do we know for a fact that Kilgrave is 100% dead??

I mean he is introduced to us by Jessica saying “He’s back” as in and we come to learn he faked a death certificate. Like yes, we see him lying there, but I would definitely assume he was lying there after he got hit by a bus, so how are we expected to know that this time its permanent?

Not to mention, don’t you think he would’ve set up safeguards against that? Why didn’t the whole city fall apart when he was threatened/killed? He had more protection when she kidnapped him earlier in the season.

Additionally, he heals faster than the average person. I mean, he’s essentially a living virus and, at that point, he’s stronger than he’s ever been. So how can he be taken out that easily?

summary: I made a new Doctor Who friend recently and I guess I somehow forgot to mention the time I met David Tennant and Billie Piper at...
body:
I made a new Doctor Who friend recently and I guess I somehow forgot to mention the time I met David Tennant and Billie Piper at comic con so anyway she comes to my house for the first time and she’s looking around admiring the decor in my room until her eyes glance upon the Family Portrait Featuring David&Billie hanging there above my fish tank and it took her a second to recognize my face among the group and she had this full moment of WAIT A MINUTE WAIT A MINUTE

WWAAAAIIITTT A MINUTTTEEE
